.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]Enamel Pin\f[R] - a 4k procedural graphics executable for 64-bit
Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
[\f[B]SAMPLES=\f[R]_number_] \f[B]enamelpin-by-suricrasiaonline\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]Enamel Pin\f[R] is a 4-kilobyte executable graphics production
(exegfx) that renders a high-resolution image procedurally.
.PD 0
.P
.PD
It was developed by Suricrasia Online and won first place in the 4k
procedural graphics competition at Solskogen 2020.
.PP
The demo generates a 1920x1080 image.
On smaller displays, the image will be clipped.
On larger displays, it will render in the corner.
.PP
Exit at any time using the \f[B]Esc\f[R] key or your window
manager\[cq]s close window shortcut.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
While \f[V]enamel_pin\f[R] itself does not accept command-line options,
you can control the rendering quality through the \f[B]SAMPLES\f[R]
environment variable:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[V]SAMPLES=100\f[R] (default)
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Controls the number of samples used during rendering.
.PP
Example:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
env SAMPLES=200 ./enamel_pin
\f[R]
.fi
